# m6_p09_ice_deadly.shot — M6 P09
#
# Regression for the two M6 P09 simulation fixes the user flagged:
#   - DEADLY tile damages on contact (not just on full-volume penetration)
#   - ICE tile actually slides (friction=1.0 + per-particle damp override)
#
# Scenario: Concourse. Paint a 10-tile-wide ICE strip and a 4-tile-wide
# DEADLY strip side by side, well below any of concourse's existing
# atrium geometry. Spawn mech above the ICE strip, walk RIGHT, release
# input over the ICE — pelvis should keep sliding for ~2 s before
# stopping. Walk onto the DEADLY tiles — HP should tick down at 5 HP/s.

window 1920 1080
seed   42 42
out    build/shots/m6_p09_ice_deadly

map concourse

# ICE strip: 12 tiles wide at row 35.
paint_rect 30 35 42 36 0x03      # SOLID | ICE
# DEADLY strip: 6 tiles wide, adjacent right.
paint_rect 42 35 48 36 0x05      # SOLID | DEADLY

# Spawn the mech directly above the DEADLY tiles (tile 44 = x=1408).
# Pelvis above the strip top so the mech falls + lands on DEADLY.
spawn_at 1408 1000
mouse    1500 540

# t=60   — mech has landed on DEADLY tiles, HP starts dropping.
# t=180  — ~2 s of contact = ~10 HP gone, multiple "1" damage numbers.
# t=300  — ~4 s of contact = ~20 HP gone.
# t=420  — long contact — HP visibly low.
at  60  shot 1_landed_deadly
at 180  shot 2_taking_damage
at 300  shot 3_visibly_hurt
at 420  shot 4_long_exposure
at 460  end

contact_sheet ice_deadly cols 2 cell 960 540
